            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-08-01T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-08-01T02:00:00-05:00" n="968" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d968">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Stuart, J. Leighton: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-08-01T15:00:00+08:00">August 1, 1949—3 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 1—12:47 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1671. Philip Fugh July 20 handed Huang Hua written memorandum stating US
                    Government position with regard to shop guarantee procedure as stated Deptel
                    890, July 27. Huang read memorandum but returned it on usual ground no
                    diplomatic relations between US and People’s Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
